  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (0e6c8fb 2022-05-21T03:23:31.545158869Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge install\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nWhen doing a `forge install`, if I have changes added to the index, those changes get committed. Forge should refuse to install a dependency if the working tree has modifications or if there are changes in the index, unless `--no-commit` is specified.",
